song.lyrics:
[V] 1My heart is hungry, my spirit doth thirst; 2Thou art the food and the water of life, 3Thou art the Word with God’s fulness in Thee, 4Thou from the heavens as food camest down, 5Thou in the word art the Spirit and life, 6Now to enjoy Thee I come to Thy Word, 7Feeding and drinking, Lord Jesus, of Thee, 8Here, O my Lord, may I fest upon Thee;
1I come to Thee, Lord to seek Thy supply; 2Thou canst revive me, my spirit upbear; 3Thou too the Spirit that God my life be; 4Thou to be drink has been smitten for me; 5Thus by the Word I may feed upon thee; 6On Thee to feed til my hunger is o’er. 7Feeding by reading, and drinking by prayer; 8Flood with Thy Spirit and fill by Thy Word;
1All that I need is none other but Thee, 2I long to eat and to dring here of Thee, 3Thee in the Word I enjoy as my food, 4Thou as the food, my exhaustless supply, 5Thou dost as Spirit in my spirit live, 6Now in my spirit I turn unto Thee, 7Reading and praying, I eat and I drink, 8May, Lord, Thou be such a feast unto me
1Thou canst my hunger and thirst satisfy. 2Thyself enjoy through my reading and prayer 3Thou as the Spirit art water to me. 4Thou as the water, a stream unto me. 5Thus I may dring in the spirit of Thee. 6Of Thee to drink till I’m thirsty no more. 7Praying and reading - Lord, Thou art my fare. 8As man hath never enjoyed nor e’re heard.
[C] Feed me, Lord Jesus, give me to drink, Fill all my hunger, quench all my thirst; Flood me with joy, be the strength of my life, Fill all my hunger, quench all my thirst.
